metadata.name: Crypto Relic #0728
metadata.description:
If you think NFTs are fascinating, then hold onto your rosary! The extended universe of Catholic saints and their surviving relics are going to blow your mind and probably make you gag a little at the same time. Believe it or not, extremely collectible mummified chunks of actual human beings are being stored in gilded glass cases right this instant in the dark dusty basements of churches around the globe. Personally, I find this both fascinating and slightly problematic, thus I propose a fun alternative!

The holy mission of Our Lady of Non-Fungibility is to offer you a chance to experience the charm of a canonized relic without traveling to Rome and being told that this lock of hair is definitely 100% for sure from the armpit of St. Sebastian. Instead, you can acquire your very own unique relic based upon the actual human body and actual canonized saints from throughout history all with a fun pixel art aesthetic. Plus, you can rest easy knowing that your relic is one of a kind and that some neighboring cathedral isn't claiming the same holy toenail as you! These tokens are meant to be fun and affordable with new editions in the works for future collecting. All artwork is hand drawn by me and all of the relevant research for this project was completed via cursory Google searches and surface-level Wikipedia dives. So, have fun and hopefully you won’t take this as seriously as the Vatican might…

Exactly 6,300 unique relic combinations are possible!

To learn more about your new relic and the saint that it came from, feel free to visit my website below!
https://joshuabellas.myportfolio.com/our-lady-of-non-fungibility-1

Happy collecting and may the Crypto Gods have mercy on your soul.
